14
00:01:56,490 --> 00:02:04,070
The POSIX subsystem (which was actually just
a description of UNIX-like systems standards)

15
00:02:04,070 --> 00:02:14,489
was included in Microsoft Windows NT because
in the 1980s the US federal government required

16
00:02:14,489 --> 00:02:20,959
